'''''Star Wars Insider'' 59''' is the fifty-ninth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[April 2]], [[2002]]. This issue celebrated the twenty-fifth anniversary of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise in the lead-up to the theatrical release of the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*A Word From George Lucas
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Prequel Update|''Attack of the Clones'' Update]] {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[Gamescape]] &mdash; Enter the Arena {{C|by [[Michael Mikaelian]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; Living the [[The New Jedi Order: Enemy Lines I: Rebel Dream|''Rebel Dream'']] {{C|by Jason Fry}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; ''Attack of the Clones'' {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*[[Set Piece]]: Rebel Alliance Briefing Room {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]] and [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Midnight Madness: Episode II {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; The ''Other'' Sci-Fi Work {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[The Last Page]]

===Features===
*"[[Han Solo: Ford Tough]]" {{C|by [[Michael G. Ryan]]}}
*:<small>It's hard to imagine a world without Harrison Ford as Han Solo or Indiana Jones. Also, ''Insider'' catches up with Peter Mayhew, the man behind the mighty Chewbacca.</small>
*"[[Princess Leia: When Carrie Met Leia]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Anyone could have guessed that Carrie Fisher was destined for stardom, but no one could have predicted how.</small>
*"[[Luke Skywalker: From Jedi to Joker]]" {{C|by [[Cory J. Herndon]]}}
*:<small>Everything you ''thought'' you knew about Mark Hamill.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in Rogue Squadron]]" {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*:<small>The New Republic's elite starfighter farce has fought Death Stars, AT-ATs, Yuuzhan Vong, and countless other threats to the galaxy.</small>
*"[[A Cast of Thousands: The Making of The New Essential Guide to Star Wars Characters|A Cast of Thousands: The Making of The New Essential Guide to ''Star Wars'' Characters]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>You can thank ''Attack of the Clones'' for this new edition of Del Rey's popular ''Essential Guide to Characters''. ''Insider'' has two entries you can't find anywhere else.</small>
*"[[Skywalker Scrapbook]]" {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*:<small>Lucy Autrey Wilson has been a Lucasfilm employee as long as there's been a Lucasfilm.</small>
*"[[Following the Bantha Tracks|Following the ''Bantha Tracks'']]" {{C|by [[Chris Fawcett]]}}
*:<small>Before ''Star Wars Insider'', there was a little newsletter called ''Bantha Tracks''.</small>

